                        <h3>Images with optional caption</h3>

                        <p>
                            <img class="size-full wp-image-3406 alignnone" src="https://via.placeholder.com/1280x720&text=Align:none" alt="">
                        </p>

                        <p>Setting the alignment to "None" will make the image
                            sit on the same baseline as the text and whilst the
                            image appears similar to the Left aligned option it
                            won't allow the text to wrap around it.</p>

                        <p>
                            <img class="size-full wp-image-3406 alignleft" src="https://via.placeholder.com/1280x720&text=Align:left" alt="">
                        </p>

                        <p>Left alignment wrap the text around the image so it
                            fits in with the flow of your content.</p>

                        <p>
